    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h2>Fixed in javadoc tool from 15.0.2</h2>\n<p>This issue now appears to be fixed when using javadoc tool from 15.0.2.</p>\n<p>That is, we no longer need to escape the @ character when using javadoc multiline <code>{@code ... }</code> block.</p>\n<p>There is a JDK bug logged <a href=\"https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8130754\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8130754</a> ... which is currently not marked as fixed but it no longer reproduces with javadoc 15.0.2.</p>\n"
  } ],
